The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing geometry from time-resolved optical impulse responses, which is a topic that falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) domains. The use of convolutional feed-forward networks for solving the reconstruction problem efficiently suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the fact that the method is applied to experimental datasets suggests that it may also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
